snippet.textDisplay: Boys, trust me as an LFC fan i know only too well how shit it is not being in the champions league. However, missing out on Europe completely is a blessing in disguise tbh, there comes a point where you need to stop trying to win the europa every season and just play in the league every weekend. When we nearly won the league in 13/14 it was because we had no European football, it helped us massively, our squad wasn't good/big enough for the number of games you play in europe. In Klopps first full season we had no European football and it gave us chance to regroup, let klopp get a few players in and start coaching his style/philosophy. We ended up coming 4th, that wouldn't have happened if we had to play in europa aswell. Heads up, I really think arteta will end up being a great coach, he just needs the time and backing from the owners. Btw London is and always has been RED, up the gooners!!

snippet.textDisplay: This is the first interview with DT I’ve disagreed with massively. We have been playing incredibly well under Arteta. ‘Rotten from top to bottom’? How? We was undefeated for 3 months until last night. We’re playing 10x better and have a clear cut direction of where we’re trying to go. That team we played last night was leggy and you can’t blame them. Saka played the full 120 minutes. 60-70 the last game and the full 90 the game before, all in the space of a week. Leno cost us the game, fact. People always say ‘well he has saved us in other games so don’t blame him’ behave..... he cost us the game, he has made multiple mistakes when in possession of the ball that has less to scoring opportunities and goals that have cost us games. You can’t make excuses for such a piss poor decision like that. This NEEDS to be a blessing, where we have just the premier league to focus on now so there’s no excuses of tiredness. If Kroenke doesn’t back Arteta in the summer with some serious serious money, there will be riots.

snippet.textDisplay: I hate to say it, but Mustafi stood out, he was our best player on the night, outside of Auba's ridiculous bicycle kick. Mustafi was consistent, all of his passes were snappy, and he was moving the ball quickly. Everyone else was meandering on the ball, slow to react  (think back to Xhaka's hesitation when Saka made that run and then crossed it to Laca to score that disallowed goal). If Xhaka didn't always take two seconds to pass, he would have hit Saka when he was onside, and we would have been a goal up much earlier. Arteta has a lot of work to do, he needs to give Martinelli, Guendouzi,  and Maitland-Niles more chances. This was exactly the type of match that Guendouzi would have stepped up in and lead us to a victory.
